						               													<description>Want to get your feet in the mud? This is your chance!&amp;#10;You and your friends are hired to work on a farm.&amp;#10;You&amp;rsquo;ll have to do different jobs every season to produce food. The more you produce the more you'll get paid, but be careful not to overdo it, because you might not keep up!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;FARMING WITH FRIENDS let&amp;rsquo;s you walk around the farm, which is divided into the four seasons. On the outer ring of the board is the sun, which will move to next month at the end of each round. Every turn you&amp;rsquo;ll have to choose what jobs you will do and how far you will advance. If you don't keep up with time you&amp;rsquo;ll be late for next season, and missing a job in the cycle of a product is something you can&amp;rsquo;t afford.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 6 farm products to be made: Bread, apples and milk for breakfast and meat, potatoes and cauliflower for dinner.&amp;#10;The game ends after 4 years or if any player has earned coins for every product. There are also bonus coins to be earned if you've helped to produce all products in a meal. The player with the most coins at the end of the game wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Farming with friends is an easy to learn family game that will teach you more about working with the seasons, and the origin of food.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
